:"England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Stighull was born about 1320, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Muriel Thorber. He died about 1372, in his hometown, at the age of 54."},"et":{"Abt 1320–Abt 1372":"umbes 1320–umbes 1372","1322–1375":"1322–1375","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1320–1372":"1320–1372","Abt 1372":"umbes 1372","1322":"1322","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1320":"1320","1397":"1397","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1372":"1372","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1320–Abt 1372":"noin 1320–noin 1372","1322–1375":"1322–1375","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1320–1372":"1320–1372","Abt 1372":"noin 1372","1322":"1322","Abt 1320":"noin 1320","1320":"1320","1397":"1397","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1372":"1372","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1320–Abt 1372":"environ 1320–environ 1372","1322–1375":"1322–1375","1